    "content": "Expand $(2x + 1)^4$ in descending powers of $x$ and simplify your\nanswer.",
    "markScheme": "Using Pascal triangle\n![SkillUpp Image](https://assets.revisionvillage.com/public/question/186561dc-7c53-4bef-b9cc-7a867881c1ea/images/1ac85e2d-06d7-4c46-8525-a36deed1bafc/d6143401ad9783a3554c63b7ab804d89d1d7b5f1.svg)\n\n\nwe get\n\n$$\n\\begin{aligned}\n\\hspace{2em} (2x + 1)^4 &= (2x)^4 + 4(2x)^3(1) + 6(2x)^2(1)^2 + 4(2x)(1)^3 + (1)^4 \\\\[9pt]\n&= 16x^4 + 4(8x^3) + 6(4x^2) + 4(2x) + 1 \\\\[9pt]\n&\\answer{= 16x^4 + 32x^3 + 24x^2 + 8x + 1}\\end{aligned}\n$$\n",
